  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To test the association between anti-Chlamydia serum titers and anti-Mycoplasma antibodies
      with Acute Coronary Syndromes.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      One hundred and twenty-six patients were divided into 4 groups: Acute Coronary Syndrome with
      ST-elevation, Non-ST-elevation, stable coronary artery disease, and individuals without
      coronary disease. Anti-Chlamydia and anti-Mycoplasma IgG antibodies were measured at baseline
      and after 6 months.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
